statements.documentation:
using the transferFrom function for transfering the particular token,
from the user address to the contract.
Here we are using the IERC20(_token) because we are using the IERC20 interface to wrap the token address
so that we can call the required functions for that token

_amount: amount of token you want to stake
_token: contract address of the token that you want to stake

Function that allows the admin to add address to the list of allowed tokens that can be staked
_token: address for the token address to be allowed for staking

_token: address of token for checking the status

addAllowedTokens(address).notice: Function that allows the admin to add address to the list of allowed tokens that can be staked _token: address for the token address to be allowed for staking

issueToken().notice: Function for issuing reward tokens to stakers based on their total value locked

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.
